The paper deals with the problem of distributed hypothesis testing, which involves information theory and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of side-information, which falls under cs.SI (Signal Processing). The use of hierarchical ensembles and expurgated bounds suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), which deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia data. The paper also involves the study of trade-offs and optimization, which are common themes in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
